
				History

versions Beta To numerous to count thru 1990. Crash city!

version 1.00  Launched in october 1991
version 1.01  Corrected error in Streak routine and a few typos in the 
	      Combination suggestions. 
	      November 1991
version 1.02  Introduction of opening requester and a more direct route 
	      to game play. 
	      January 1992.
version 1.10  Drastic modification of accompanying script for Font 
	      Mover. Script now provides safe exit without any
              changes being made to disk. Also it does not crush 
	      existing directories. Sorry about that! 
	      March 1992
version 1.11  System 2.0x compatability assured. 
	      Slight modifications to Palette required. 
	      April 1992
version 1.12  Fudging of backspaced characters eliminated.
	      April 1992
version 1.13  Cleaned up Screen Layout.
	      Corrected rounding error in Low Darts routine.
	      More fudging eliminated.
	      Introduced "version" keyword. 
	      July 1992
version 1.14  Fixed serious bug (unexpected exception) in speech module.
	      Reworked Preview mode.
	      Streamlined code; worked on speed.
	      Added more checks on user input especially during Check-Out.
	      August 1992
version 1.15  Fixed annoying bug in Player verification routine.
	      Added notice of file length during player entry.
	      Added more colors to stats screen layouts.
	      August 1992
	      
